# No long dashes

- **Never use the em dash (—)** in UI copy, docs, JSON content, or code comments.
- Use a **hyphen (-)** or **en dash (–)** only when needed for ranges (e.g. "2020–2021").
- For pauses or asides in prose, rephrase with commas, parentheses, or separate sentences.

### Examples

- **Bad:** "No registration required—no sign-up."
- **Good:** "No registration required; no sign-up." or "No registration required. No sign-up."
- **Bad:** "We want to make the interview engaging—pick what fits you."
- **Good:** "We want to make the interview engaging. Pick what fits you."
